Description: Align stack to 16 bytes before C callbacks from demo trampolines
 The assembly trampolines (basictramp, farshowptramp, farmalloctramp,
 fardointtramp) switch the stack pointer back to the saved C stack
 (saveESP) before calling their C counterparts.  saveESP was captured
 inside startdemo after a pushad (32 bytes), so its alignment relative
 to the 16-byte boundary is not guaranteed to satisfy the i386 System V
 ABI requirement (ESP % 16 == 0 at a call site).
 .
 SDL2 and other modern libraries are compiled with SSE support and emit
 movaps instructions that require 16-byte aligned stack slots.  The
 misaligned stack caused a SIGSEGV inside libSDL2 on the first
 farshowp → IXDRV_CopyScreen → SDL_RenderPresent call.
 .
 Fix: add "and esp, -16" after restoring saveESP in every trampoline,
 immediately before the call to the C function.  This rounds ESP down
 to a 16-byte boundary; the call instruction then subtracts 4 more
 bytes, yielding ESP % 16 == 12 at function entry as required by the ABI.
